Synctl version 0.1.0
====================

The Synctl module is an rsync based incremental backup tool. The way it make
backups is controlled by configuration files (profiles), allowing to backup
different parts of your computer with different parameters.

This module is provided with the synctl executable which you can use to list,
make and restore backups from the command line.

INSTALLATION

To install this module type the following:

   perl Makefile.PL
   make
   make test
   make install

DEPENDENCIES

This module requires these other modules and libraries:

  rsync        (only for client)
  openssh
  
